I’ve confirmed why the funding leg failed: the chosen 0x selectors are not implemented on this proxy at the fork block. I’m probing two things now in a local fork test: whether Bento already has LP for the swapper, and which 0x selectors succeed when called through the vulnerable `swap()` path.
